Parking space counter with OpenCV
=================================


1. Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
OpenCV (Open Source Computer Vision Library) is a widely used open source library for image processing and computer vision. It provides a set of functions and tools to perform a variety of tasks.


2. Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
- first step, install virtual environment
$ virtualenv venv
$ source venv/bin/activate

- install dependencies
$ pip install -r requirements.txt


3. Using script
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
When executing manager_parking_lots.py we have an interface to configure spaces with the left mouse button to draw a rectangle of a space, and with the right button to delete the rectangle. To save changes, simply press the Q key.

Running main script the video is running opencv will monitor frame by frame and update the vacancies that are empty and filled on the screen.


6. References
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
